re that if the production metadata doesn't include ICU4J, the native compile could fail. Maybe I should add the dependency and review the metadata to see how it’s structured. I wonder if I need to preserve anything.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering collation in H2**\\n\\nI'm thinking about collation strength in H2, specifically how it might ignore accents and case. I wonder if collation only applies for ordering and not equality. Maybe using ORDER BY can help? I should check the table operations with the collator. I could query INFORMATION_SCHEMA.SETTINGS, but I'm unsure about comparing. To cover this, maybe I need to assert that the setting exists and consider using SELECT SETTING_VALUE for COLLATION. Directly using CompareMode might also simplify things.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_XE34ViIY1Hj1CXLz73xZzVDe|fc_0d626a89b73a827d0169f4cd8581d0819cba17b1a791d848b9", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find ~/.gradle/caches/modules-2/files-2.1/com.ibm.icu/icu4j -maxdepth 1 -mindepth 1 -type d 2>/dev/null | sed 's#.*/##' | sort -V | tail -20", "timeout": 10}, "partialJson": "{\"command\":\"find ~/.gradle/caches/modules-2/files-2.1/com.ibm.icu/icu4j -maxdepth 1 -mindepth 1 -type d 2>/dev/null | sed 's#.*/##' | sort -V | tail -20\",\"timeout\":10}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1539, "output": 1774, "cacheRead": 45056, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 48369, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777651053382, "responseId": "resp_0d626a89b73a827d0169f4cd6e3260819cbf7626a01add2097"}}
