e necessary!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Reviewing reflection configuration**\\n\\nI'm looking into the existing reflect-config, which includes classes like `org.h2.Driver`; I see they're not in production. It raises the question of whether I need to add ICU4J reflect for production metadata or if it’s okay to add it to the test reflect-config too. Avoiding duplication is ideal, but since the native image relies on repository metadata, it might be safer to include it in tests as well. Still, I wonder if that broadens access unnecessarily.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Writing a test for ICU4J**\\n\\nI'm considering whether the dependency version for the artifact is hardcoded in the test inputs. It seems it's not, so I need to write a test. I think package names are necessary, and I will look at the existing tests in the h2 package. The top-level class should be public and I'll use AssertJ for assertions. The method types will be annotated nicely. I’ll specifically test the configuration for ICU4J collators across supported locale name forms.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_iL3oT2FsLF8hXFFHdB1puIeB|fc_0d626a89b73a827d0169f4cdae4940819cb6b25cbd7f96682f", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.h2database/h2/2.1.210/src/test/java/h2/CompareModeIcu4JTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage h2;\n\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport java.sql.Connection;\nimport java.sql.DriverManager;\nimport java.sql.ResultSet;\nimport java.sql.SQLException;\nimport java.sql.Statement;\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\nimport java.util.List;\nimport java.util.UUID;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class CompareModeIcu4JTest {\n    @Test\n    void configuresIcu4jCollatorsForSupportedLocaleNameForms() throws SQLException {\n        assertIcu4jCollationCanBeInstalled(\"ICU4J_EN\", \"PRIMARY\");\n        assertIcu4jCollationCanBeInstalled(\"ICU4J_EN_US\", \"SECONDARY\");\n        assertIcu4jCollationCanBeInstalled(\"ICU4J_ENGLISH\", \"TERTIARY\");\n    }\n\n    private static void assertIcu4jCollationCanBeInstalled(String collation, String strength) throws SQLException {\n        String databaseName = \"icu4j\" + UUID.randomUUID().toString().replace(\"-\", \"\");\n        try (Connection connection = DriverManager.getConnection(\"jdbc:h2:mem:\" + databaseName);\n                Statement statement = connection.createStatement()) {\n            statement.execute(\"SET COLLATION \" + collation + \" STRENGTH \" + strength);\n\n            assertCollationSetting(statement, collation, strength);\n\n            statement.execute(\"CREATE TABLE words(value VARCHAR)\");\n            statement.execute(\"INSERT INTO words(value) VALUES ('Zulu'), ('alpha'), ('Echo')\");\n            try (ResultSet resultSet = statement.executeQuery(\"SELECT value FROM words ORDER BY value\")) {\n                assertThat(readValues(resultSet)).containsExactlyInAnyOrder(\"Zulu\", \"alpha\", \"Echo\");\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static void assertCollationSetting(Statement statement, String collation, String strength) throws SQLException {\n        try (ResultSet resultSet = statement.executeQuery(\"\"\"\n                SELECT SETTING_VALUE\n                FROM INFORMATION_SCHEMA.SETTINGS\n                WHERE SETTING_NAME = 'COLLATION'\n                \"\"\")) {\n            assertThat(resultSet.next()).isTrue();\n            assertThat(resultSet.getString(1)).isEqualTo(collation + \" STRENGTH \" + strength);\n            assertThat(resultSet.next()).isFalse();\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static List<String> readValues(ResultSet resultSet) throws SQLException {\n        List<String> values = new ArrayList<>();\n        while (resultSet.next()) {\n            values.add(resultSet.getString(1));\n        }\n        return values;\n    }\n}\n"}, "partialJson": "{\"path\":\"tests/src/com.h2database/h2/2.1.210/src/test/java/h2/CompareModeIcu4JTest.java\",\"content\":\"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage h2;\\n\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\n\\nimport java.sql.Connection;\\nimport java.sql.DriverManager;\\nimport java.sql.ResultSet;\\nimport java.sql.SQLException;\\nimport java.sql.Statement;\\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\\nimport java.util.List;\\nimport java.util.UUID;\\n\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\n\\npublic class CompareModeIcu4JTest {\\n    @Test\\n    void configuresIcu4jCollatorsForSupportedLocaleNameForms() throws SQLException {\\n        assertIcu4jCollationCanBeInstalled(\\\"ICU4J_EN\\\", \\\"PRIMARY\\\");\\n        assertIcu4jCollationCanBeInstalled(\\\"ICU4J_EN_US\\\", \\\"SECONDARY\\\");\\n        assertIcu4jCollationCanBeInstalled(\\\"ICU4J_ENGLISH\\\", \\\"TERTIARY\\\");\\n    }\\n\\n    private static void assertIcu4jCollationCanBeInstalled(String collation, String strength) throws SQLException {\\n        String databaseName = \\\"icu4j\\\" + UUID.randomUUID().toString().replace(\\\"-\\\", \\\"\\\");\\n        try (Connection connection = DriverManager.getConnection(\\\"jdbc:h2:mem:\\\" + databaseName);\\n                Statement statement = connection.createStatement()) {\\n            statement.execute(\\\"SET COLLATION \\\" + collation + \\\" STRENGTH \\\" + strength);\\n\\n            assertCollationSetting(statement, collation, strength);\\n\\n            statement.execute(\\\"CREATE TABLE words(value VARCHAR)\\\");\\n            statement.execute(\\\"INSERT INTO words(value) VALUES ('Zulu'), ('alpha'), ('Echo')\\\");\\n            try (ResultSet resultSet = statement.executeQuery